column2: Sunny; 3-4" of rain last 5-6 days; slight wind
Cool breeze; 55 degree air temp; just after a 3 day rain
Beautiful day starting to warm slightly- a little more cloudy at 2: 00
Some algae but beautiful calm day with good sun
Slight breeze- but beautiful day- no rain or storms for several days.
It has been real hot for 2 weeks- the upper part of flowage really getting good algae bloom.  Pea soup.  Nice sunny day today- little wind.
Improvement over the 24th + 4th of July.  It was very bad then.  Some rain lately.
Pretty good swimming conditions- but still a lot of algae.  When it rains the dam opens and worst stuff moves out.  No rain and algae builds up.
Bad algae bloom still on the jump river.  Our winds have been from the west and south and holding the stuff up there.  The Chippewa's heavy flow clears quickly.
Floods last week May have stained water more than usual.  No algae.
A lot of rain this last week.
Algae level increasing on south end of lake due to wind.
Partly cloudy- wind 4-5 mph- 68 degrees.  Quiet on the lake- very little boat traffic
Partly cloudy- winds light and variable at 2-4 mph-  temp 74 degrees- no boat traffic
